This product bundles third-party reference DATA under `src/gpcr_tools/data/`, each
licensed separately from the Apache-2.0 source code. These data files retain their
respective licenses; any redistribution must preserve the attribution below and
comply with the share-alike / database terms.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. src/gpcr_tools/data/gpcrdb_generic_numbers.json.gz
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A residue generic-numbering and segment table derived from GPCRdb.

Source:      GPCRdb -- https://gpcrdb.org
License:     Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
             https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
Attribution: GPCRdb (https://gpcrdb.org). The generic residue-numbering scheme is
             from Isberg et al., "Generic GPCR residue numbers - aligning topology
             maps while minding the gaps", Trends in Pharmacological Sciences, 2015.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. src/gpcr_tools/data/gtopdb_endogenous_ligands.json.gz
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A flat set of endogenous-ligand InChIKeys and PubChem CIDs derived from the
IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY (GtoPdb), version 2026.1.

Source:      IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY -- https://www.guidetopharmacology.org
License:     The GtoPdb database is licensed under the Open Data Commons Open
             Database License (ODbL, https://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/);
             its contents are licensed under the Creative Commons
             Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License (CC BY-SA 4.0,
             https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/).
Attribution: IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY (https://www.guidetopharmacology.org).

To rebuild this artifact from the current GtoPdb release, run
`python3 scripts/build_endogenous_table.py`.
